1
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:11,233
[ CLINKING ]

2
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:29,666
[ BELLS TOLLING ]

3
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:33,033
YOU WANT TO KNOW MY BIRTHDAY?

4
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:35,866
YEP, IF YOU DON'T MIND.
SO WHEN IS IT?

5
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:38,766
MY BIRTHDAY IS ON MARCH 6.

6
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,833
MM-HMM. MM-HMM.
WHAT'S YOUR BLOOD TYPE?

7
00:00:40,866 --> 00:00:42,200
B, I THINK.

8
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,200
UH-HUH. SHIROKU MOKUSEI.
YUP.

9
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:46,766
PISCES, TYPE B,
FIVE ELEMENTS, WOOD.

10
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,233
AND I HAVE YOUR RESULTS!

11
00:00:53,266 --> 00:00:56,900
YOU'RE A ROMANTIC WHO LIKES TO
FOLLOW THE BEAT OF HER OWN DRUM.

12
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:59,900
YOU GOT BIG, BIG GOALS,
YOU'RE AN OPTIMIST
AND YOU LOVE TO DAYDREAM.

13
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:01,566
HUH?

14
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,166
OH!

15
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,366
HOW ABOUT YOU,
IZUMO?

16
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:09,300
MY BIRTHDAY'S OCTOBER 11,
I'M TYPE A.

17
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:15,566
AND I HAVE YOUR RESULTS!

18
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:19,666
IZUMO, YOU'RE AN IDEALIST,
AND YOU TREAT EVERYONE
FAIR AND SQUARE.

19
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:22,866
BUT EVEN THOUGH YOU PLAY NICE
WITH EVERYONE, YOU'RE ALSO
SUPER QUICK TO CRITICIZE...

20
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:26,066
ANYTHING OR ANYONE
WHO FORCES YOU
TO QUESTION YOUR OWN BELIEFS.

21
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:28,933
- RAD!
- WHAT THE HELL
WAS THAT ABOUT?

22
00:01:28,966 --> 00:01:32,666
THAT'S YOUR ASTROLOGICAL SIGN,
YOUR BLOOD TYPE
AND THE FOUR PILLARS OF DESTINY.

23
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,266
THE FORTUNE COMES OUTTA HERE.

24
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:37,566
YOUR STUDIES WOULD BENEFIT
FROM THOSE MEMORIZATION SKILLS.

25
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:41,433
THAT'S WHAT YOU SAY,
BUT YOU GOTTA ADMIT--
YOU'RE INTERESTED, AREN'T YA?

26
00:01:41,466 --> 00:01:42,433
[ HUFFS ]

27
00:01:42,466 --> 00:01:43,533
I'M OUTTA HERE.

28
00:01:43,566 --> 00:01:46,066
SHE IS ONE COLD WOMAN.

29
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,766
DO ME.
TELL MY FORTUNE NEXT.

30
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,466
NOPE.
DOESN'T WORK FOR GUYS.

31
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:53,433
- HOW COME?
- I'M A SPECIALIST.

32
00:01:53,466 --> 00:01:55,666
GIRL FORTUNES ONLY.

33
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:57,266
GUYS DON'T INSPIRE ME.

34
00:01:57,300 --> 00:01:59,066
COME ON.
LET ME TELL YOU
MY BIRTHDAY.

35
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:00,633
I TOLD YOU,
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

36
00:02:00,666 --> 00:02:04,766
I NEVER THOUGHT ABOUT IT BEFORE,
BUT HOW WOULD A SON OF SATAN
BE BORN?

37
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,500
WHO KNOWS?
[ SHIEMI SHRIEKS ]

38
00:02:07,533 --> 00:02:09,100
UH, YOU OKAY?

39
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:13,733
AH, I JUST REALIZED
KAMIKI'S BIRTHDAY IS COMING UP.

40
00:02:31,766 --> 00:02:34,000
♪ [ MEN SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

41
00:03:49,504 --> 00:03:53,104
SO, ANYWAY, WE'RE GOING TO THROW
A SURPRISE BIRTHDAY PARTY
FOR KAMIKI,

42
00:03:53,138 --> 00:03:54,604
AND IT'LL BE
THE BEST EVER.

43
00:03:54,638 --> 00:03:57,604
OF ALL THE PEOPLE,
WHY DO WE HAVE TO CELEBRATE
HER BIRTHDAY?

44
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:02,171
UH, EXCUSE ME, BON.
WE ALL VOTED FOR IT,
SO NO COMPLAINING.

45
00:04:02,204 --> 00:04:05,104
OKAY, I'M GOING TO ASSIGN
EACH OF YOU A TASK.

46
00:04:08,504 --> 00:04:09,938
[ ALL ]
HUH?

47
00:04:09,971 --> 00:04:11,738
[ WHIMPERS ]

48
00:04:11,771 --> 00:04:14,171
ONE THING BEFORE WE START.

49
00:04:14,204 --> 00:04:17,504
- WHAT HAPPENS
AT PARTIES AGAIN?
- [ SHOUTING ]

50
00:04:17,538 --> 00:04:20,338
THERE'S PRESENTS,
THEN THERE'S A CAKE.

51
00:04:20,371 --> 00:04:22,838
AND THERE'S
ALWAYS SNACKS
AND DRINKS TOO.

52
00:04:22,871 --> 00:04:24,104
AND DECORATIONS
AND STUFF.

53
00:04:24,138 --> 00:04:26,704
OH, THAT'S RIGHT!
A PRESENT.

54
00:04:26,738 --> 00:04:29,038
WHAT CAN WE GET HER
THAT SHE'LL BE SURE TO LIKE?

55
00:04:29,071 --> 00:04:30,838
MEAT'S A GOOD PRESENT.
HUH?

56
00:04:30,871 --> 00:04:32,304
BARBECUE, SUKIYAKI.

57
00:04:32,338 --> 00:04:34,071
OH, AND ROAST BEEF TOO.
[ SIGHS ]

58
00:04:34,104 --> 00:04:36,338
SO PRETTY MUCH
ALL THE STUFF
YOU WANT TO EAT?

59
00:04:36,371 --> 00:04:39,771
AND OVEN-ROASTED TURKEY.
THROW THAT ON THE TABLE,
AND IT'S A PARTY.

60
00:04:39,804 --> 00:04:42,338
NOT THAT I'VE EVER SEEN
OVEN-ROASTED TURKEY BEFORE.

61
00:04:42,371 --> 00:04:45,238
OKUMURA, YOUR MENU'S
OUT OF CONTROL.

62
00:04:45,271 --> 00:04:48,204
HEY, I THINK
A BOUQUET OF FLOWERS
WOULD BE AWESOME.

63
00:04:48,238 --> 00:04:51,871
[ GIGGLES ]
THANK YOU, SHIMA.
YOU'RE SWEET.

64
00:04:51,904 --> 00:04:53,304
[ KAMIKI GASPS ]
YOU CAN'T EAT FLOWERS!

65
00:04:53,338 --> 00:04:57,171
RIN! THERE ARE LOTS OF FLOWERS
THAT ARE PERFECTLY EDIBLE.

66
00:04:57,204 --> 00:04:59,138
IN SPRINGTIME
THERE'S ALL KINDS
OF DIFFERENT FLOWERS--

67
00:04:59,171 --> 00:05:01,271
CALM DOWN, MORIYAMA.

68
00:05:01,304 --> 00:05:04,438
OH, MY GOD!
WOULD YOU CUT THE CRAP ALREADY?

69
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:06,671
SHIMA, YOU'RE IN CHARGE
OF THE PRESENT.

70
00:05:06,704 --> 00:05:09,138
FIGURE OUT WHAT SHE WANTS,
AND GET IT BY SUNDAY.

71
00:05:09,171 --> 00:05:11,771
GOTCHA.
OKUMURA, YOU'RE
ON CAKE DETAIL.

72
00:05:11,804 --> 00:05:13,304
NOT BUYING IT,
BAKING IT.

73
00:05:13,338 --> 00:05:16,571
YOU GOT IT.
I'VE NEVER BAKED A CAKE BEFORE,
BUT WHATEVER.

74
00:05:16,604 --> 00:05:17,838
[ GROWLS ]
HUH?

75
00:05:17,871 --> 00:05:19,504
KONEKOMARU,
YOU'RE IN CHARGE...

76
00:05:19,538 --> 00:05:22,138
OF SHOPPING
AND OKUMURA.
HUH?

77
00:05:22,171 --> 00:05:24,604
THAT LEAVES MORIYAMA AND ME
TO DECORATE THE ROOM.

78
00:05:24,638 --> 00:05:26,304
[ SHIEMI ] OKAY!
[ SHIMA ]
THAT'S OUR BON.

79
00:05:26,338 --> 00:05:28,471
HE'S GOT
MAD LEADERSHIP SKILLS.

80
00:05:28,504 --> 00:05:33,438
UH, BON, IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
I COULD DO BESIDES, UH--

81
00:05:33,471 --> 00:05:36,971
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT, MAN.
NO ONE KNOWS
JAPANESE SWEETS LIKE YOU,

82
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:38,638
SO WITH THOSE SKILLS,
YOU'RE GOLDEN.

83
00:05:38,671 --> 00:05:41,738
BUT CAKES AND JAPANESE SWEETS
ARE COMPLETELY DIFF--

84
00:05:41,771 --> 00:05:43,171
YOU SO GOT THIS.

85
00:05:43,204 --> 00:05:45,538
WE'RE GONNA MAKE
A GREAT TEAM, KONEKOMARU.

86
00:05:45,571 --> 00:05:47,471
UH--

87
00:05:47,504 --> 00:05:48,704
SURE.

88
00:05:48,738 --> 00:05:50,338
[ SUGURO ]
OKAY, PEOPLE,

89
00:05:50,371 --> 00:05:52,871
IF SHE CATCHES US GETTING READY
FOR THE PARTY, IT'S OVER.

90
00:05:52,904 --> 00:05:54,771
SO STAY SHARP
AND WATCH YOUR BACKS.

91
00:05:54,804 --> 00:05:56,504
"PARTY" ON THREE.
ONE, TWO, THREE.

92
00:05:56,538 --> 00:05:57,604
[ ALL ]
PARTY!

93
00:05:57,638 --> 00:06:00,038
HMM.

94
00:06:00,071 --> 00:06:03,571
A BIRTHDAY PARTY.
HUH.

95
00:06:07,504 --> 00:06:09,304
HUH? WHOA!

96
00:06:12,604 --> 00:06:14,504
- HMM.
- OH, HI, SHIMA.

97
00:06:14,538 --> 00:06:16,804
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAND
OUT THERE.
COME ON IN.

98
00:06:16,838 --> 00:06:19,071
OH, WELL,
IS PAKU AROUND?

99
00:06:19,104 --> 00:06:21,104
HMM.
OH.

100
00:06:21,138 --> 00:06:23,804
SHE'S BACK.
PAKU!

101
00:06:23,838 --> 00:06:24,804
HUH?

102
00:06:24,838 --> 00:06:25,804
HMM?

103
00:06:25,838 --> 00:06:27,104
[ GASPS ]

104
00:06:28,338 --> 00:06:30,071
[ GIGGLING ]

105
00:06:30,704 --> 00:06:31,771
[ SHIMA HUMMING ]

106
00:06:34,504 --> 00:06:36,871
WHAT'S GOING ON?
YOU GOT A MINUTE?

107
00:06:36,904 --> 00:06:39,071
LET'S GO OUTSIDE.
THE WALLS HAVE EARS.

108
00:06:40,838 --> 00:06:43,238
DO YOU THINK THEY'RE--
YOU KNOW?

109
00:06:43,271 --> 00:06:44,104
YEAH.

110
00:06:44,804 --> 00:06:46,871
[ SIGHS ]

111
00:06:46,904 --> 00:06:49,304
[ SHIMA ] SORRY TO PULL YOU
OUTTA CLASS LIKE THAT.
[ PAKU ] IT'S OKAY.

112
00:06:49,338 --> 00:06:51,938
AH, YOU'RE THE BEST, PAKU.
SERIOUSLY.

113
00:06:51,971 --> 00:06:55,371
YOU'RE BOTH PRETTY
AND AMAZING.
[ HUFFS ]

114
00:06:59,604 --> 00:07:01,038
[ MIWA ]
OKAY, OKUMURA.

115
00:07:01,071 --> 00:07:02,938
READ THE RECIPE,
AND I'LL WRITE IT DOWN.

116
00:07:02,971 --> 00:07:04,038
[ RIN ]
HERE GOES.

117
00:07:04,071 --> 00:07:07,204
"FOUR EGGS, ONE CUP OF SUGAR,

118
00:07:07,238 --> 00:07:09,438
TWO CUPS OF FLOUR,
THREE-QUARTERS"--
[ GASPS ]

119
00:07:09,471 --> 00:07:11,871
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS DOING?
[ GASPS ]

120
00:07:11,904 --> 00:07:14,504
GOOD LUCK, SOLDIER.
[ GRUNTS ]

121
00:07:14,538 --> 00:07:15,738
[ BLUBBERING ]

122
00:07:15,771 --> 00:07:17,704
YEAH.
HUH?

123
00:07:17,738 --> 00:07:19,404
WE WEREN'T DOING ANYTHING!

124
00:07:19,438 --> 00:07:21,104
OOH! SEE YA!

125
00:07:22,004 --> 00:07:24,071
HUH?

126
00:07:27,538 --> 00:07:29,271
[ CHUCKLES ]

127
00:07:29,304 --> 00:07:31,171
OH!

128
00:07:31,204 --> 00:07:32,904
NOW THAT'S A DECORATION.

129
00:07:32,938 --> 00:07:34,904
THIS IS AMAZING, SUGURO!

130
00:07:34,938 --> 00:07:37,204
YOU'RE SO GOOD
AT DOING CRAFTS.

131
00:07:37,238 --> 00:07:39,138
WELL, YEAH.
[ GASPS ]

132
00:07:39,171 --> 00:07:41,338
OH, OH!
HMM?

133
00:07:41,371 --> 00:07:42,404
[ GASPS ]

134
00:07:42,438 --> 00:07:45,371
- WHAT ARE YOU GUYS DOING?
- [ BOTH STAMMERING ]

135
00:07:45,404 --> 00:07:47,671
UH--
IT'S NONE OF YOUR
BUSINESS, OKAY?

136
00:07:47,704 --> 00:07:48,838
[ GRUNTS ]
[ GASPS ]

137
00:07:48,871 --> 00:07:51,204
WAIT FOR ME, SUGURO!

138
00:07:54,271 --> 00:07:56,538
WHAT DID HE MEAN
BY THAT?

139
00:08:08,729 --> 00:08:10,696
SO ARE YOU GOING OUT WITH HIM
OR WHAT?

140
00:08:10,729 --> 00:08:13,162
WHO?
DURING LUNCH TODAY,

141
00:08:13,196 --> 00:08:15,396
THE TWO OF YOU
WERE CHATTING UP A STORM.

142
00:08:15,429 --> 00:08:17,462
HUH? SHIMA?
NO WAY.

143
00:08:17,496 --> 00:08:20,029
- ARE YOU SURE?
- YES, I SWEAR.

144
00:08:20,062 --> 00:08:22,396
WE WERE JUST DISCUSSING
THE BIR--

145
00:08:22,429 --> 00:08:25,329
- BIR?
- THE-THE BIRDS OF PREY.

146
00:08:25,362 --> 00:08:27,129
HE WAS ASKING ME ABOUT THEM.

147
00:08:27,162 --> 00:08:28,362
[ SQUAWKING ]

148
00:08:28,396 --> 00:08:29,829
[ SIGHS ]

149
00:08:29,862 --> 00:08:32,662
IF YOU SAY SO.
WHATEVER.

150
00:08:32,696 --> 00:08:34,596
LISTEN, THAT CLOWN'S
THE WRONG GUY FOR YOU.

151
00:08:34,629 --> 00:08:37,096
[ GIGGLES ]

152
00:08:40,762 --> 00:08:42,562
HMM?
WHAT ARE YOU MAKING, RIN?

153
00:08:42,596 --> 00:08:44,262
IT'S A BIRTHDAY CAKE.

154
00:08:44,296 --> 00:08:46,629
A BIRTHDAY CAKE?

155
00:08:46,662 --> 00:08:49,662
WHAT'S A CAKE?
YOU'LL SEE IN A MINUTE.

156
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,429
[ WHISKING ]

157
00:08:51,462 --> 00:08:54,329
[ MIWA, THINKING ]
AFTER WHAT HAPPENED
THE OTHER DAY,

158
00:08:57,796 --> 00:08:59,696
BEING ALONE WITH HIM IS...

159
00:08:59,729 --> 00:09:02,429
<i>REALLY AWKWARD.</i>
[ WHISKING CONTINUES ]

160
00:09:04,796 --> 00:09:06,829
OKAY, WHAT'S NEXT?

161
00:09:06,862 --> 00:09:08,396
OH, RIGHT!
UH,

162
00:09:08,429 --> 00:09:11,162
"SIFT THE FLOUR
AS YOU ADD IT
TO THE REST OF THE MIX."

163
00:09:11,196 --> 00:09:12,762
UH, I-I-I'LL DO THAT.

164
00:09:14,396 --> 00:09:16,129
AWESOME.
WAY TO SIFT.

165
00:09:16,162 --> 00:09:18,362
SURE YOU NEVER BAKED
A CAKE BEFORE?

166
00:09:18,396 --> 00:09:20,296
OH, I-I LEARNED IT
BY WATCHING.

167
00:09:20,329 --> 00:09:24,429
SPEAKING OF WHICH, IF THIS IS
THE FIRST TIME YOU EVER BAKED
A CAKE, I COULDN'T TELL.

168
00:09:24,462 --> 00:09:26,496
YOU MUST BE NATURALLY TALENTED.

169
00:09:26,529 --> 00:09:28,096
OH, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT.

170
00:09:28,129 --> 00:09:31,029
I GREW UP
IN A HOUSE FULL OF GUYS,
AND THEY ALL SUCKED AT COOKING.

171
00:09:31,062 --> 00:09:33,529
I DIDN'T REALLY HAVE A CHOICE.
I HAD TO LEARN HOW TO DO IT.

172
00:09:33,562 --> 00:09:35,896
OH.
READY.
COOL.

173
00:09:37,196 --> 00:09:41,062
YEAH, IT'S ONE THING
IF YOU'RE COOKING FOR YOURSELF,

174
00:09:41,096 --> 00:09:43,862
BUT IT'S A LOT MORE FUN
WHEN YOU COOK FOR SOMEONE ELSE,
YOU KNOW?

175
00:09:43,896 --> 00:09:46,462
- THAT'S WHAT I THINK
ANYWAY.
- HMM.

176
00:09:46,496 --> 00:09:48,129
YEAH, GOOD POINT.

177
00:09:48,162 --> 00:09:51,862
RIGHT! GET READY TO BAKE
THE AWESOMEST CAKE EVER,
KONEKOMARU.

178
00:09:51,896 --> 00:09:53,862
[ MIWA ]
DON'T STIR IT LIKE THAT!

179
00:09:53,896 --> 00:09:57,529
SPONGE CAKES ARE ALL ABOUT AIR.
STIR IT GENTLY. GENTLY.

180
00:09:57,562 --> 00:09:59,296
LIKE, UH, THIS?
KEEP MOVING YOUR HANDS.

181
00:09:59,329 --> 00:10:00,296
YES, SIR.

182
00:10:03,162 --> 00:10:04,762
[ SHIEMI HUMMING ]

183
00:10:04,796 --> 00:10:07,462
[ GIGGLES ]
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

184
00:10:07,496 --> 00:10:09,262
[ YUKIO ]
WORKING HARD?
[ GASPS ]

185
00:10:09,296 --> 00:10:12,029
YUKI.
I GOT A MESSAGE
THIS MORNING...

186
00:10:12,062 --> 00:10:13,829
ABOUT AN ORDER
OF MEDICINAL HERBS.

187
00:10:13,862 --> 00:10:15,496
I CAME BY
TO PICK THEM UP.

188
00:10:15,529 --> 00:10:17,662
HOLD ON.
I'LL GO TAKE A LOOK.

189
00:10:17,696 --> 00:10:20,429
TRUE CROSS ACADEMY
DEMON PHARMACEUTICS.

190
00:10:20,462 --> 00:10:21,829
UH--
DEMON PHARMACEUTICS.

191
00:10:21,862 --> 00:10:24,162
ACTUALLY, I ORDERED THOSE
FOR PERSONAL USE.

192
00:10:24,196 --> 00:10:28,129
REALLY?
THAT'S UNUSUAL.
LET'S SEE.

193
00:10:28,162 --> 00:10:31,629
[ DRAWER OPENS ]
I HEARD ABOUT THE PARTY
YOU'RE THROWING,

194
00:10:31,662 --> 00:10:34,162
AND I ALSO HEARD
THAT IT WAS YOUR IDEA.

195
00:10:34,196 --> 00:10:37,062
I'M SURE KAMIKI
IS GONNA LOVE IT.

196
00:10:37,096 --> 00:10:40,362
WELL, IT'S SORT OF
FOR ME TOO.
HMM?

197
00:10:40,396 --> 00:10:43,596
MY GRANDMA AND MOM ALWAYS DID
SOMETHING SPECIAL FOR ME...

198
00:10:43,629 --> 00:10:45,796
WHENEVER MY BIRTHDAY
CAME AROUND,

199
00:10:45,829 --> 00:10:48,462
BUT I NEVER GOT TO HAVE A PARTY
WITH FRIENDS AND STUFF.

200
00:10:48,496 --> 00:10:50,829
NOW THAT I'M GOING
TO THE CRAM SCHOOL,

201
00:10:50,862 --> 00:10:53,129
I'VE HAD A CHANCE
TO MAKE SOME FRIENDS.

202
00:10:53,162 --> 00:10:57,329
AND SO I FIGURED NOW
WAS A GOOD TIME TO GET EVERYONE
TOGETHER AND HAVE A PARTY.

203
00:10:57,362 --> 00:10:58,596
[ CHUCKLES ]

204
00:10:58,629 --> 00:11:00,629
IT'S KIND OF SELFISH, ISN'T IT?

205
00:11:00,662 --> 00:11:03,362
IT'S NOT.
I THINK IT'S A GREAT IDEA.

206
00:11:03,396 --> 00:11:05,329
BY THE WAY,

207
00:11:05,362 --> 00:11:06,796
WHEN'S YOUR BIRTHDAY?

208
00:11:06,829 --> 00:11:10,862
I MEAN, YOU AND RIN.
OH, IT'S DECEMBER THE 27TH.

209
00:11:10,896 --> 00:11:13,929
HAVE YOU AND RIN EVER HAD
A BIRTHDAY PARTY BEFORE?

210
00:11:13,962 --> 00:11:16,462
YES, YOU COULD SAY THAT.
SORT OF.

211
00:11:16,496 --> 00:11:18,629
SORT OF HOW?

212
00:11:18,662 --> 00:11:21,096
SINCE OUR BIRTHDAY
IS RIGHT AFTER CHRISTMAS,

213
00:11:21,129 --> 00:11:23,396
WE'D CELEBRATE BOTH OF THEM
ON THE SAME NIGHT.

214
00:11:23,429 --> 00:11:27,262
EVERYONE AT THE MONASTERY
WOULD COME TO THE PARTY.

215
00:11:27,296 --> 00:11:31,896
BUT FOR SOME REASON
I NEVER CARED THAT MUCH
ABOUT MY BIRTHDAY.

216
00:11:31,929 --> 00:11:33,129
HMM.

217
00:11:33,162 --> 00:11:36,462
ANYWAY, I HOPE
YOUR PARTY GOES WELL.

218
00:11:37,862 --> 00:11:40,996
MM-HMM.
AND IF YOU WANT,
YOU COULD COME TOO, YUKI.

219
00:11:41,029 --> 00:11:42,896
I KNOW IT'LL BE REAL FUN.

220
00:11:53,419 --> 00:11:56,053
[ ALL GASPING ]

221
00:12:01,061 --> 00:12:02,528
WHAT IS THIS?

222
00:12:02,561 --> 00:12:04,495
IT'S JUST A PROTOTYPE
I WHIPPED UP.

223
00:12:04,528 --> 00:12:06,561
THIS SUCKER LOOKS BADASS,
DOESN'T IT?

224
00:12:06,595 --> 00:12:08,961
[ GROWLING ]
WRONG, WRONG, WRONG!

225
00:12:08,995 --> 00:12:11,095
[ GROWLING ]
WHAT? YOU DON'T LIKE
ANGEL FOOD?

226
00:12:11,128 --> 00:12:15,328
WHAT ARE YOU, BLIND?
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
IN CHARGE OF HIM, KONEKOMARU.

227
00:12:15,361 --> 00:12:18,428
I KNOW, BUT HE MADE IT
WHEN I WASN'T LOOKING.

228
00:12:18,461 --> 00:12:20,361
HEY, EASE UP
ON KONEKOMARU.

229
00:12:20,395 --> 00:12:22,295
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHAT'S WRONG WITH IT,

230
00:12:22,328 --> 00:12:23,895
'CAUSE I THINK I MADE
A MASTERPIECE.

231
00:12:23,928 --> 00:12:25,028
NO. YOU MADE A MISTAKE.

232
00:12:25,061 --> 00:12:27,661
I DON'T SEE WHAT THE PROBLEM IS.

233
00:12:27,695 --> 00:12:31,595
TO ME IT LOOKS LIKE
A PERFECTLY GOOD BIRTHDAY CAKE.

234
00:12:31,628 --> 00:12:33,395
[ ALL ]
HUH?

235
00:12:35,261 --> 00:12:39,528
OH, MY GOD. BIRTHDAY CAKES
AND CHRISTMAS CAKES
<i>ARE</i> TOTALLY DIFFERENT.

236
00:12:39,561 --> 00:12:42,128
AND IT TOOK US 15 YEARS
TO REALIZE IT.

237
00:12:42,161 --> 00:12:43,595
OH, RIN.

238
00:12:43,628 --> 00:12:45,695
SO WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
WITH THIS THING?

239
00:12:45,728 --> 00:12:48,495
[ RIN ]
"FROM ALL OF US
AT THE CRAM SCHOOL,

240
00:12:48,528 --> 00:12:53,495
PLEASE ACCEPT THIS AS A HUMBLE
TOKEN OF OUR APPRECIATION."

241
00:12:53,528 --> 00:12:56,828
[ MEPHISTO ]
A CAKE CELEBRATING
THE BIRTH OF CHRIST FOR ME?

242
00:12:56,861 --> 00:12:58,728
A DEMON?

243
00:12:58,761 --> 00:13:00,995
HMM. HMM.

244
00:13:02,095 --> 00:13:03,895
AH.

245
00:13:03,928 --> 00:13:07,295
WHOA! IT'S FANTASTIC!

246
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,295
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

247
00:13:09,328 --> 00:13:11,761
THANKS FOR WAITING.
NO, NOT AT ALL.

248
00:13:11,795 --> 00:13:15,695
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHOA, YOU EVEN LOOK FOXY
IN YOUR STREET CLOTHES.

249
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:17,161
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

250
00:13:17,195 --> 00:13:19,595
- COME ON, LET'S GO.
- LEAD ON.

251
00:13:22,628 --> 00:13:23,695
[ PANTING ]

252
00:13:26,795 --> 00:13:29,895
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS IS HAPPENING AFTER ALL
THE WARNINGS I GAVE HER.

253
00:13:40,428 --> 00:13:41,861
[ FOOTSTEPS RUNNING ]

254
00:13:41,895 --> 00:13:43,195
[ GRUNTS ]

255
00:13:43,228 --> 00:13:44,228
HMM?

256
00:13:44,261 --> 00:13:46,928
IS SOMETHING WRONG?
HUH?

257
00:13:46,961 --> 00:13:48,328
OH, NO, IT'S NOTHING.

258
00:13:48,361 --> 00:13:50,695
[ GIGGLES ]
SHIMA, YOU'RE WEIRD.

259
00:13:53,828 --> 00:13:56,828
- WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF THIS ONE?
- YEAH, IT'S PRETTY COOL.

260
00:13:58,428 --> 00:14:01,495
WATCH IT.
DON'T GET SO CLOSE.
[ GASPS ]

261
00:14:04,095 --> 00:14:05,628
[ GASPING ]

262
00:14:09,861 --> 00:14:13,361
I THINK IZUMO'S TRYING
TO COLLECT ALL THE FIGURES
FROM THIS SERIES.

263
00:14:13,395 --> 00:14:17,061
OH, YEAH?
OH, LOOK AT THOSE BIG EYES--
SO CUTE.

264
00:14:17,095 --> 00:14:21,728
SO CUTE. SO CUTE. <i>SO CUTE.</i>

265
00:14:21,761 --> 00:14:23,295
HE SAID SHE'S CUTE!

266
00:14:23,328 --> 00:14:25,995
I COULD FALL IN LOVE
WITH IT.

267
00:14:26,028 --> 00:14:29,361
IN LOVE. IN LOVE. IN LOVE.

268
00:14:29,395 --> 00:14:31,995
[ KAMIKI GASPS ]
IN LOVE?

269
00:14:34,428 --> 00:14:36,795
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THEY'VE FALLEN IN LOVE.

270
00:14:36,828 --> 00:14:41,795
THEY'RE GOING WAY TOO FAST.
THEY DON'T KNOW EACH OTHER
THAT WELL.

271
00:14:41,828 --> 00:14:42,828
WHERE'D THEY GO?

272
00:14:45,895 --> 00:14:47,995
[ PANTING ]

273
00:14:51,861 --> 00:14:53,495
UH-OH, IT'S RAINING.

274
00:14:53,528 --> 00:14:56,128
AW, DARN IT.
I DIDN'T BRING
AN UMBRELLA ALONG TODAY.

275
00:14:56,161 --> 00:14:58,595
HAVE NO FEAR.
I'VE GOT JUST WHAT
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

276
00:15:01,661 --> 00:15:02,661
[ GASPS ]

277
00:15:05,761 --> 00:15:08,261
[ GASPS ]
THEY'RE SHARING AN UMBRELLA!

278
00:15:08,295 --> 00:15:10,495
OH.
OH, WHAT'S WRONG?

279
00:15:10,528 --> 00:15:12,861
OH, SOMETHING GOT
IN MY EYE, IS ALL.

280
00:15:12,895 --> 00:15:14,361
HERE, LET ME SEE.

281
00:15:15,761 --> 00:15:16,895
[ SHRIEKING ]

282
00:15:19,695 --> 00:15:21,361
[ WHIMPERING ]

283
00:15:22,895 --> 00:15:24,928
[ WHIMPERING ]

284
00:15:24,961 --> 00:15:27,961
NO! NO!

285
00:15:28,795 --> 00:15:31,128
[ GASPS ]

286
00:15:31,161 --> 00:15:33,961
[ KAMIKI SHRIEKING ]

287
00:15:33,995 --> 00:15:36,995
THERE. I GOT IT.
WHOA!

288
00:15:37,028 --> 00:15:38,561
[ GROANS ]
I-IZUMO?

289
00:15:38,595 --> 00:15:41,328
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

290
00:15:41,361 --> 00:15:43,061
[ BOTH ]
UH--

291
00:15:43,095 --> 00:15:45,061
GUESS SHE CAUGHT US.
[ LAUGHS ]

292
00:15:45,095 --> 00:15:46,861
I WASN'T TRYING TO CATCH ANYONE.

293
00:15:46,895 --> 00:15:49,928
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?
TRYING TO KISS PAKU
IN THE MIDDLE...

294
00:15:49,961 --> 00:15:51,461
OF THE STREET...

295
00:15:51,495 --> 00:15:53,461
WHERE EVERYONE CAN SEE?

296
00:15:53,495 --> 00:15:55,961
HUH? I WASN'T TRYING
TO KISS HER.

297
00:15:55,995 --> 00:15:57,828
HE WASN'T TRYING
TO KISS ME.

298
00:15:57,861 --> 00:16:00,861
THEN WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHY ARE YOU GUYS
SNEAKING AROUND?

299
00:16:00,895 --> 00:16:04,928
WE WEREN'T SNEAKING AROUND.
WE WERE TRYING TO FIND
A BIRTHDAY PRES...

300
00:16:04,961 --> 00:16:07,761
ENT.

301
00:16:07,795 --> 00:16:09,595
[ THUNDERCLAP ]

302
00:16:09,628 --> 00:16:13,628
I SWEAR IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.
I SORTA LET THE CAT
OUT OF THE BAG.

303
00:16:13,661 --> 00:16:15,961
NICE JOB, YOU DUMBASS.
WAY TO GO.

304
00:16:15,995 --> 00:16:17,128
I'M SORRY.

305
00:16:17,161 --> 00:16:19,461
BUT I DON'T GET IT.
WHY ARE YOU MAD?

306
00:16:19,495 --> 00:16:21,561
YOU HANG ME OUT TO DRY
LIKE THIS?

307
00:16:21,595 --> 00:16:23,461
WELL, I'M NOT GONNA LET
YOU GET AWAY WITH IT.

308
00:16:23,495 --> 00:16:26,061
[ SUGURO ]
CHILL OUT.
NO ONE'S HANGING ANYTHING.

309
00:16:26,095 --> 00:16:27,461
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

310
00:16:27,495 --> 00:16:30,628
YOU'RE USING ME AS AN EXCUSE
JUST SO YOU CAN ALL GO HAVE FUN.

311
00:16:30,661 --> 00:16:34,128
BUT, IZUMO,
YOU SHOULD BE HAPPY.
WE'RE DOING THIS FOR YOU.

312
00:16:34,161 --> 00:16:37,395
I'M SORRY.
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

313
00:16:37,428 --> 00:16:39,295
I SAID WE SHOULD THROW YOU
A BIRTHDAY PARTY,

314
00:16:39,328 --> 00:16:41,095
AND I WANTED IT
TO BE A SURPRISE.

315
00:16:41,128 --> 00:16:44,828
YOU SHOULDN'T BE APOLOGIZING.
YOU KNOW, MORIYAMA WORKED HARD
TO MAKE YOU HAPPY.

316
00:16:44,861 --> 00:16:46,228
SO WHAT'S WITH THE ATTITUDE?

317
00:16:46,261 --> 00:16:50,395
IS IT REALLY SUCH A DRAG
THAT EVERYONE WANTS TO CELEBRATE
YOUR BIRTHDAY?

318
00:16:50,428 --> 00:16:52,528
NO. IT'S NOT A DRAG.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEAN.

319
00:16:52,561 --> 00:16:54,128
[ SUGURO ]
THEN WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

320
00:16:54,161 --> 00:16:56,928
I'M JUST SAYING
IT'S UNFAIR, IS ALL.

321
00:16:56,961 --> 00:16:58,661
[ ALL ]
UNFAIR?

322
00:16:58,695 --> 00:17:01,795
ALL THESE MONTHS GO BY,
AND NOW YOU WANT TO THROW
A PARTY FOR ME?

323
00:17:01,828 --> 00:17:05,428
HOW UNFAIR IS THAT?
WHAT ABOUT
EVERYONE ELSE'S BIRTHDAYS?

324
00:17:05,461 --> 00:17:07,928
HOW MANY HAVE WE SKIPPED
SINCE THE FIRST DAY
OF CLASS, HUH?

325
00:17:07,961 --> 00:17:09,461
[ ALL GASP ]

326
00:17:09,495 --> 00:17:12,428
I'M SURE A COUPLE OF YOU
TURNED 16 BY NOW.
AM I WRONG?

327
00:17:12,461 --> 00:17:16,395
THE OTHER DAY, YOU GUYS
WERE TALKING ABOUT GETTING
YOUR MOTORCYCLE LICENSES.

328
00:17:16,428 --> 00:17:19,395
I GOTTA HAND IT
TO YOU, IZUMO.
YOU'RE SHARP.

329
00:17:19,428 --> 00:17:21,195
THERE, SEE?
I KNEW IT.

330
00:17:21,228 --> 00:17:25,195
IF YOU WANT TO THROW A PARTY,
LET'S DO IT RIGHT AND CELEBRATE
EVERYONE'S BIRTHDAY.

331
00:17:25,228 --> 00:17:27,361
OTHERWISE, YOU CAN
FORGET ABOUT MINE.

332
00:17:27,395 --> 00:17:28,795
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

333
00:17:28,828 --> 00:17:33,595
THEN IT'LL BE BON'S
AND SHIMA'S AND KAMIKI'S.

334
00:17:33,628 --> 00:17:35,028
PAKU'S TOO.

335
00:17:35,061 --> 00:17:37,695
THAT MEANS WE'LL HAVE TO GET
FOUR BIRTHDAY PRESENTS.

336
00:17:37,728 --> 00:17:40,261
WE HAVE TO MAKE SURE
IT'S FAIR FOR EVERYONE,

337
00:17:40,295 --> 00:17:42,895
SO WE'LL GIVE BACK SUGURO
AND SHIMA'S MONEY.

338
00:17:42,928 --> 00:17:44,495
THEN-- THEN---

339
00:17:44,528 --> 00:17:46,461
MAN, IS THIS GONNA BE
A PAIN IN THE BUTT.

340
00:17:46,495 --> 00:17:51,628
HEY, WHAT DO YOU GUYS THINK
ABOUT INCLUDING PEOPLE WHOSE
BIRTHDAYS ARE COMING UP SOON?

341
00:17:51,661 --> 00:17:56,295
YOU KNOW, 'CAUSE THAT WAY
WE CAN CELEBRATE
EVERYONE'S BIRTHDAY TOGETHER.

342
00:18:05,828 --> 00:18:08,461
[ GASPS ]
I HAVE NO IDEA
HOW TO SPELL THIS.

343
00:18:08,495 --> 00:18:10,861
NO WORRIES.
I CAN SPELL IT FOR YOU.

344
00:18:10,895 --> 00:18:15,495
YOU READY?
UH, H-A-P-P-Y.

345
00:18:18,861 --> 00:18:20,461
ALL RIGHT.
IT'S DONE.

346
00:18:20,495 --> 00:18:22,761
SO DOES
EVERYONE
HAVE SOMETHING TO DRINK?

347
00:18:22,795 --> 00:18:24,961
MM-HMM.
[ RIN ]
IT'S READY!

348
00:18:24,995 --> 00:18:26,361
HEY, HURRY UP. WE'RE HUNGRY.

349
00:18:26,395 --> 00:18:28,995
DID YOU BAKE THAT CAKE
BY YOURSELF?

350
00:18:29,028 --> 00:18:33,495
YEAH, I COULDN'T DO
ANYTHING ELSE 'CAUSE COOKING'S
THE ONLY PRODUCTIVE SKILL I GOT.

351
00:18:33,528 --> 00:18:35,328
[ LAUGHS ]
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE ADMITTED THAT.

352
00:18:41,795 --> 00:18:42,961
[ ALL GASPING ]

353
00:18:42,995 --> 00:18:44,628
FLASH!

354
00:18:44,661 --> 00:18:46,028
[ GRUNTING ]

355
00:18:47,861 --> 00:18:50,061
[ SHOUTING ]

356
00:18:50,095 --> 00:18:51,261
[ GRUNTS ]

357
00:18:51,295 --> 00:18:53,028
[ GASPS ]
KONEKOMARU!

358
00:18:53,061 --> 00:18:54,828
[ GROANS ]

359
00:18:54,861 --> 00:18:57,661
[ CHUCKLES ]

360
00:18:57,695 --> 00:18:59,495
[ ALL CHEERING ]

361
00:19:02,395 --> 00:19:05,328
THANKS A LOT.
THAT WAS AWESOME.

362
00:19:06,828 --> 00:19:09,428
[ LAUGHS ]

363
00:19:19,961 --> 00:19:21,795
[ SHIEMI ]
THREE, TWO--

364
00:19:21,828 --> 00:19:24,295
[ ALL ]
HAPPY BIRTHDAY!

365
00:19:27,928 --> 00:19:30,095
[ SHIMA ]
THIS IS THE MOMENT
YOU'VE BEEN WAITING FOR.

366
00:19:30,128 --> 00:19:31,861
TIME FOR PRESENTS.

367
00:19:31,895 --> 00:19:34,995
YOU WON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
GETTING TILL YOU'VE DRAWN
A NUMBER FROM THE BOX.

368
00:19:35,028 --> 00:19:36,161
SO WHO WANTS TO GO FIRST?

369
00:19:36,195 --> 00:19:38,761
OH, ME! I WILL!
I'LL GO FIRST.

370
00:19:38,795 --> 00:19:40,495
[ GIGGLING ]

371
00:19:46,128 --> 00:19:48,428
IS EVERYTHING OKAY, YUKI?

372
00:19:48,461 --> 00:19:51,395
SURE. EVERYONE LOOKS
LIKE THEY'RE HAVING FUN.

373
00:19:51,428 --> 00:19:54,761
HOW ABOUT YOU?
ARE YOU HAVING FUN TOO?

374
00:19:54,795 --> 00:19:56,595
OF COURSE I AM.

375
00:19:57,961 --> 00:20:01,095
YOU'VE BEEN ACTING
SO STRANGE LATELY.
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

376
00:20:01,128 --> 00:20:07,061
AS KIDS, RIN AND I
WERE ALWAYS TOLD OUR BIRTHDAYS
WERE ON DECEMBER THE 27TH.

377
00:20:07,095 --> 00:20:08,761
BUT IT NEVER SEEMED REAL TO US.

378
00:20:08,795 --> 00:20:12,528
COME ON, PICK NUMBER ONE.
WE DON'T KNOW WHEN WE WERE
REALLY BORN OR WHERE.

379
00:20:12,561 --> 00:20:14,395
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO OUR MOTHER WAS.

380
00:20:14,428 --> 00:20:17,628
- ALL RIGHT!
- HUH?

381
00:20:17,661 --> 00:20:21,061
[ YOUNG RIN ]
COME ON, DAD,
TELL US ABOUT MOM.

382
00:20:21,095 --> 00:20:22,595
WHAT WAS SHE LIKE?

383
00:20:22,628 --> 00:20:25,861
I DON'T KNOW.
I PICKED YOU GUYS UP
UNDER A BRIDGE.

384
00:20:25,895 --> 00:20:28,028
OH, NOT AGAIN.

385
00:20:28,061 --> 00:20:32,161
IT'S THE TRUTH. IT WAS WINTER,
AND A WATERMELON THIS BIG
CAME FLOATING DOWN THE RIVER.

386
00:20:32,195 --> 00:20:35,728
AND WHEN I SPLIT
THAT SUCKER OPEN, I FOUND
THE TWO OF YOU INSIDE IT.

387
00:20:35,761 --> 00:20:38,095
FOR REALS?
YEAH, I REMEMBER
THERE WAS ALL THIS TALK...

388
00:20:38,128 --> 00:20:40,561
ABOUT WHETHER I SHOULD SLICE IT
VERTICALLY OR HORIZONTALLY.

389
00:20:40,595 --> 00:20:45,428
IF I CUT INTO THAT MELON
THE WRONG WAY OR IF I WAS OFF
A BIT, I'D WHACK YOU IN HALF.

390
00:20:45,461 --> 00:20:47,228
AW, COME ON, DAD!

391
00:20:47,261 --> 00:20:50,095
[ YUKIO ]
MY FATHER ALWAYS EVADED
THE SUBJECT,

392
00:20:50,128 --> 00:20:52,295
AND HE NEVER TOLD US
THE TRUTH ABOUT HER.

393
00:20:53,395 --> 00:20:55,395
HE CAME CLOSE ONCE.

394
00:21:01,095 --> 00:21:03,028
[ GASPING ]

395
00:21:03,061 --> 00:21:06,728
[ FUJIMOTO ]
THE FIRST TIME I MET YOU BOYS
IT WAS SNOWING, JUST LIKE TODAY.

396
00:21:06,761 --> 00:21:07,895
HUH?

397
00:21:13,828 --> 00:21:16,361
BUT THAT WAS THE ONLY CLUE
WE EVER GOT FROM HIM.

398
00:21:16,395 --> 00:21:18,528
AND NOW THAT HE'S GONE,
RIN AND I HAVE NO WAY...

399
00:21:18,561 --> 00:21:21,128
OF EVER FINDING OUT
WHEN OUR REAL BIRTHDAY IS.

400
00:21:21,161 --> 00:21:22,295
[ ALL LAUGHING ]

401
00:21:22,328 --> 00:21:24,795
- HE'S SO CUTE!
- THAT'S HILARIOUS.

402
00:21:26,628 --> 00:21:27,928
YUKI?
HMM?

403
00:21:27,961 --> 00:21:30,028
I'M REALLY GLAD YOU WERE BORN.

404
00:21:30,061 --> 00:21:31,728
[ GASPS ]

405
00:21:31,761 --> 00:21:34,561
IT DOESN'T MATTER WHERE
IT HAPPENED OR WHEN.

406
00:21:34,595 --> 00:21:36,661
I'M HAPPY YOU'RE HERE
EITHER WAY.

407
00:21:40,795 --> 00:21:42,361
THANKS, SHIEMI.

408
00:21:42,395 --> 00:21:44,595
[ SHIMA ]
HEY, YOU GUYS!

409
00:21:44,628 --> 00:21:47,395
HURRY UP AND PICK ONE.
YOU'VE GOT NUMBER TWO
OR NUMBER SEVEN.

410
00:21:49,361 --> 00:21:51,028
LET'S GO.

411
00:21:55,261 --> 00:21:56,795
[ SIGHS ]

412
00:22:06,295 --> 00:22:08,928
♪ [ WOMAN SINGING
IN JAPANESE ]

413
00:23:32,695 --> 00:23:36,695
[ LAUGHING ]
NICE GLASSES, GUY!
THEY'RE PERFECT!

414
00:23:36,728 --> 00:23:38,295
[ SIGHS ]

415
00:23:38,328 --> 00:23:40,661
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]

416
00:23:40,695 --> 00:23:41,828
[ CHATTERING ]

417
00:23:41,861 --> 00:23:44,295
YES. OKUMURA SPEAKING.

418
00:23:44,328 --> 00:23:46,295
[ CHATTERING CONTINUES ]
WHAT?

419
00:23:46,328 --> 00:23:49,095
YES. RIGHT.

420
00:23:49,128 --> 00:23:51,428
UNDERSTOOD.
I'M ON THE WAY.

421
00:23:51,461 --> 00:23:55,561
- WHAT'S GOING ON, YUKIO?
- IT'S ABOUT OUR MONASTERY.

422
00:23:55,595 --> 00:23:58,195
HUH?

423
00:23:58,228 --> 00:24:01,761
IT'S BEEN ATTACKED.
[ GASPS ]

424
00:24:01,795 --> 00:24:04,995
[ RIN ]
I'M NOT GONNA LET ANYONE ELSE
GET HURT 'CAUSE OF ME.

425
00:24:05,028 --> 00:24:07,528
THIS IS MY FIGHT TOO,
SO I'M GOING.

426
00:24:07,561 --> 00:24:09,095
[ YUKIO ]
YOU'RE NOT, AND THAT'S THAT.

427
00:24:09,128 --> 00:24:11,795
[ SHURA ]
HEY, YUKIO, WHY ARE YOU
FREAKING OUT LIKE THAT?

428
00:24:11,828 --> 00:24:14,961
[ YUKIO ]
THAT'S WHAT THIS IS ABOUT?
REVENGE?

